  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7 and boil a kettle&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Slice the<strong> potatoes</strong> (skins on) into approx. 1cm thick slices</p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat and once hot, add the<strong> lamb mince</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cook for 4-5 min, breaking it up with a spoon as you go</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/223.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/223.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/223.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/223.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/223.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the<strong> potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 7 min, or until they're just about fork-tender</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely dice the<strong> onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic </strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>onion</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>cinnamon</strong> and <strong>dried oregano</strong> to the<strong> lamb mince</strong> and cook for 10 min</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/223.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/223.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/223.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/223.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/223.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice the <strong>aubergine<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into 1cm thick slices</p>\r\n<p>Add them to a baking tray and drizzle with <strong>olive oil</strong> and a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 15 min, or until cooked through, turning halfway through</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/223.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/223.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/223.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/223.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/223.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve the <strong>beef stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>\r\n<p>Stir the <strong>tomato paste</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>beef stock</strong>&nbsp;into the<strong> lamb mince</strong></p>\r\n<p>Reduce the heat to medium and cook for 10-15 min or until most of the water has evaporated</p>\r\n<p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/223.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/223.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/223.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/223.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/223.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, pop a tbsp of&nbsp;<strong>natural yoghurt</strong>&nbsp;into a mixing bowl with a drizzle of&nbsp;<strong>olive oil&nbsp;</strong>and a pinch of&nbsp;<strong>salt&nbsp;</strong>and&nbsp;<strong>pepper&nbsp;</strong>- this is your&nbsp;<strong>yoghurt dressing&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Tear the&nbsp;<strong>little gem<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;into bite-size pieces</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
